content.description: Start with crimp sidepulls (there are a few to choose from around the same height). Work up to the obvious rail. Hike your feet up and huck for the top. Very fun.
content.protection: Pads, spotter to keep you away from the tree/boulders at the base.
content.location:
Climbs the center of the inside face of a boulder standing adjacent to the cliffband, and facing the Bastard Crack. 

 There is a tree just behind you on this one.

content.description:
Awesome overhanging finger crack. Big pulls between good locks. Seems like most people reach the jugs on the right and drop off (that's what I did). You could continue up the crack or face, but it looks like it would be about a 5.10- free solo on choss.

 Start low with good finger locks, pull up, then pull up some more, then fire for the jugs up on the right and drop. If it was in Yosemite it would probably be a (sandbagged) V4, but whatever it's a great climb regardless.
content.protection: Pads, a rope if you wanted to go to the top.
content.location: Overhanging finger crack cut into a section of the main cliffband just East of the trail junction

content.description: Nice shady & secluded boulder and cliffband section right off the upper Tumalo Creek trail.
